content: So far, this app has been invaluable for helping me navigate the label reading and helping me to eat safely with my allergy.

content: Game changer! No more guessing games when it comes to food shopping with multiple food allergies.
This app has helped me greatly, newly diagnosed with Alpha Gal, this app has saved me from countless reactions. Its the best money Ive spent for sure.

My husband has Alpha-Gal and my sister has celiac. Being able to scan and check in a hurry has been a blessing. My only downside is I have often unchecked the boxes with things my hubby can tolerate with his AG such as the sugars and carranegan, but it still hits red and doesn't seem to save.
replyContent:
Thanks for 4-star review Nikki!
Ingredients can be flagged for detection in 2 ways: 1 - In one or more diets and 2 - In the master ingredient list.  Please ensure that Carrageenan is unchecked in the Alpha-gal diet AND in the master ingredient list (under Stabilizers).  If you are still having issues please contact us at CadresSoftware@gmail.com

content: App doesn't work well for allergens. Product can have "processed in facility that also handles eggs" and then app will say that the product contains eggs. Or if you scan a cereal and mentions calories with milk it then shows that the product contains milk. Actually continued using the app over the last few weeks and found it quite useful. Would give it 5 stars if it had a feature to denote the difference between containing vs processed in facility that handles x allergen product.
replyContent: The "processed in a facility"" message exists for a GOOD reason. People with severe allergies CAN have a reaction from residues remaining on processing equipment. Unlike other bar code apps, our app detects these allergens residing in this message. Regarding calories with milk, our suggestion is to refrain from scanning the Nutrition Facts label.

content: I have alpha gal and it's hard to find foods that are safe.. another thing that would help a lot of people who have alpha gal is to add a scan medicine.
replyContent:
Thanks for the 4-star review Sonya!
Many Rx drugs (e.g. Lovenox) don't clearly indicate red meat-derived ingredients. There could also be a case where a company alters a drug to include an alpha-gal ingredient without the app ever knowing about it. Including drugs in the app is simply a risk that we are not willing to take at this time.

content: AWESOME!! THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR THE ALPHA GAL DIET!!!
replyContent: Thanks for the 5-star review Melissa!  Don't hesitate to contact us if you need other ingredients added to the alpha-gal diet.

content: Would it be possible to add alpha-gal as a diet?
replyContent:
Thanks for the 5-star review James!
The new Alpha-gal diet is available as of Feb. 1, 2019.

content: Needs work-doesn't appear to save allergens ingredients and a diet simultaneously. whenbi go back in to app ibhave to recheck. Plese fix and add Alpha-gal.
replyContent:
The app is working properly.
An ingredient is available for detection if it is turned on in any diet or in the master ingredient list. Turning an ingredient on/off in one diet will not automatically turn it on/off in other diets or in the master ingredient list. This allows multiple diets to be separately maintained.
